name: Our Lady of Mt Virgin church
directions: Rear of the church (Frederick St. Side) right by the steps to the choir loft.
comment: The church isn't always open but you can get the mass schedule online, just google the church. God loves you just as you are and so do I! Come up to the choir loft and say hi. -Evan (Music Director)

name: Subway
directions: Two gendered single stall bathrooms, in the hallway to the right.
comment: I work here and I'm pretty sure no one even cares at all, just feel free to use whichever you like and don't worry about anyone saying anything.

name: Blind Cat Rescue
comment: They have a transgender friendly bathroom policy.

name: Kannarraville North Rest Area

name: Friley Residence Hall

1 unisex single occupant bathroom located on 2nd floor next to the Glenn Miller Ballroom
1 all gender restroom located on the second floor next to room 247

comment: Three unisex single-stall bathrooms. You do have to walk right past the registers so it might be awkward not to buy anything, but the cafe is usually busy enough that it won't draw attention.

name: Starbucks
directions: First hallway. Two gender neutral bathrooms.

name: Insomnia Cookies

name: Moon Time restaurant

name: La Quinta Inn

comment: Building is a laundromat, open 24/7. The bathroom itself is small and dingy, containing a single toilet and a hook for toilet paper, which might not always be there. The door is not sturdy, and while it can lock, it is not the most secure. The sink is located outside the bathroom in the open laundromat area (in front of the vending machine), and usually does not have soap or paper towels.

name: U of M Medical Center Blood Draw
U of M Medical Center Blood Draw
Levite Jewish Community Center

comment: not sure how management is, there's trans friendly employees

name: Starbucks
directions: In the back near the condiment bar, two neutral single stall restrooms, the left has a toilet and changing room and the right has a toilet and urinal.
comment: They are unlocked and anyone can use them, you don't have to buy something first, and no one will confront you about anything because they're neutral. I'm non-binary and work here because of this. Most starbucks are doing this, too.
